content:
The OmniStudio Build Tool is a Node.js command-line automation tool that packages and deploys Salesforce data packs in a source-control-friendly format. It creates a YAML manifest that describes a deployment project, enabling continuous integration of OmniStudio metadata to source control.

The Build Tool packages related objects together as data packs, preserving dependencies. For example, it requires records to have unique IDs to ensure data isn't duplicated. The tool validates data and verifies the success of data deployment.

Install and update the Build Tool by installing Node.js or through NPM. Before starting, understand available authentication methods, command syntax, and how the job file works.

Set up a project to export and deploy data between source and target orgs. To export and deploy data, follow this process. If recently installed the managed package or created a sandbox org, load metadata first.

Use the job file to specify settings, project path, what to export, and where to deploy. Review Build Tool commands for exporting and deploying, troubleshooting, and additional tasks.

When developing on a large project, use a manifest-driven workflow to track major items. Extract those items to commit to version control using the manifest section of the job file.

The OmniStudio Build Tool includes tools and processes for troubleshooting, including log files, errors, and a script for cleaning data.
title: Data Deployment with the OmniStudio Build Tool
